00133 /*
00134 Amiga:
00135     00 0000 - 0F FFFF       1MB Chip RAM
00136     BF D000 - BF DF00       8520-B  (access at even-byte addresses only)
00137         -         -
00138     BF E001 - BF EF01       8520-A  (access at odd-byte addresses only)
00139 
00140     DF F000 - DF FFFF       Chip registers.
00141     C0 0000 - D7 FFFF       Internal expansion (slow) memory (on some systems).
00142     C0 0000 - DB FFFF       Slow memory check in ROM
00143     
00144     FC 0000 - FF FFFF       256K System ROM.
00145     
00146     0000 0000 0000 xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx - chip ram
00147     0000 0000 1011 1111 11** **** **** **** - 8520-A/B
00148     0000 0000 1101 1111 1111 000x xxxx xxxx - chip registes
00149     0000 0000 1100 xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx - slow memory
00150     0000 0000 1101 0xxx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx - slow memory
00151     0000 0000 1101 10xx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx - slow memory
00152     0000 0000 1111 11xx xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx - system rom
00153     
00154     0000 0000 110* **** **** **** **** **** - chip registers and copy of chip registers
00155     
00156     0x00F00000 - no ROM at this address
00157 
00158 bus_ssram
00159     SLAVE 2: ssram memory
00160         0x00000000 - 0x001FFFFF - 1MB Chip RAM and copies
00161             0x00000000 - 0x000FFFFF - 1MB Chip RAM          -> 0x00000000 - 0x000FFFFF in SSRAM
00162             0x00100000 - 0x001FFFFF - copy of Chip RAM
00163             
00164             AND mask:           0000 0000 0000 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111
00165             overlay OR mask:    0000 0000 0001 1100 0000 0000 0000 0000
00166             
00167         0x10100000 - 0x101BFFFF - 768Kb firmware RAM        -> 0x00100000 - 0x001BFFFF in SSRAM
00168             0x10180000 - 0x101B5FFF - video buffer          -> 0x00180000 - 0x001B5FFF in SSRAM, 216*4*256
00169             0x101B6000 - 0x101BFFFF - free                  -> 0x001B6000 - 0x001BFFFF in SSRAM
00170             
00171             AND mask:           0000 0000 0001 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111
00172             
00173         0x00FC0000 - 0x00FFFFFF - 256Kb ROM                 -> 0x001C0000 - 0x001FFFFF in SSRAM
00174         
00175             AND mask:           0000 0000 0001 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111
00176 
00177 bus_sd
00178     SLAVE 1: control
00179         0x10001000 - 0x1000100F - 4 long words
00180     MASTER R1
00181     
00182 control_osd
00183     SLAVE 3: on screen display
00184         0x10000000 - 0x10000FFF - 512x8
00185     MASTER R2
00186 
00187 bus_terminator
00188     SLAVE 0:
00189         all unused addresses
00190 
00191 ao68000
00192     MASTER R3
00193 
00194 ocs_video
00195     SLAVE 4:
00196         chip registers
00197         08C-09B, 100-10B, 0E0-0F7, 120-1BF, 110-11B
00198     MASTER P1
00199 
00200 ocs_control
00201     SLAVE 5:
00202         chip registers
00203         000-007 R, 09C-09F, 010-013 R, 01C-01F R, 028-02B
00204 
00205 ocs_blitter
00206     SLAVE 6:
00207         chip registers
00208         040-059, 060-067, 070-075
00209     MASTER P2
00210 
00211 ocs_copper
00212     SLAVE 7:
00213         chip registers
00214         02C-02F, 080-08B
00215     MASTER R4
00216     
00217 cia_a
00218     SLAVE 8:
00219     0000_0000_101*_****_**10_****_****_****
00220 
00221 cia_b
00222     SLAVE 9:
00223     0000_0000_101*_****_**01_****_****_****
00224 
00225 ocs_serial
